Executive Summary

First Solar maintains a commanding 24.2% share of the U.S. utility-scale solar market with 30.1 GW of installed capacity across 688 generators. The analysis uses Cadmium Telluride (CdTe) technology as a proxy for First Solar, which is >95% accurate given First Solar's dominance in the U.S. CdTe market.

Strategic Insights

Manufacturing Proximity Advantage

First Solar shows strong market penetration in states near its manufacturing facilities:

  • Alabama (66% market share) - near Lawrence County, AL facility
  • Louisiana (45% market share) - location of Iberia Parish facility
  • Ohio markets - served by Perrysburg and Lake Township facilities

Market Opportunities

Underserved Large Markets: States with >5 GW solar but <20% First Solar penetration represent expansion opportunities. Focus on logistics optimization to serve distant markets more competitively.

High-Growth Potential States: Target markets where crystalline silicon currently dominates but where CdTe's hot climate advantages could provide competitive edge.

Recommendations

  1. Geographic Expansion
    • Target high-growth states with <20% First Solar penetration
    • Leverage hot climate advantage in Southwest expansion
  2. Manufacturing Strategy
    • Consider facility locations to serve underserved regions
    • Optimize logistics network for 1,000-2,000 km radius coverage
  3. Market Positioning
    • Emphasize domestic manufacturing advantage
    • Target utility customers prioritizing supply chain security

Important Caveats

  1. CdTe technology is used as a proxy for First Solar (>95% accurate)
  2. Early-release EIA data should not be used for official aggregations
  3. Coordinates are plant-level, not generator-level
  4. Some fields including manufacturer names are pending validation

For precise manufacturer analysis, wait for final EIA-860 release (September 2025)
